Reasoning: The paper deals with visual agents and their ability to explore and capture informative observations. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for capturing and processing visual data, as well as reinforcement learning (cs.AI) for training the agent to perform efficient exploratory behaviors. The use of recurrent neural networks also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the active completion of 3D object shapes, which could fall under robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the lack of manual labeling in training data acquisition suggests a potential application in natural language processing (cs.CL) for unsupervised learning.
